        unpublished observations). These observations suggest that
        nontypeable 
        <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">H.</ENAMEX> influenzae grows as a biofilm in
        the respiratory tract of <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">adults</ENAMEX> with <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">COPD</ENAMEX>, reminiscent of 
        Pseudomonas aeruginosa and its well
        established propensity to grow as a biofilm while causing
